### What is Flutter?

Flutter is Google's open-source UI toolkit for building natively compiled applications for mobile, web, and desktop from a single codebase.

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Language | Dart |
| Rendering | Custom engine (Skia/Impeller) |
| Platforms | Android, iOS, Web, Windows, macOS, Linux |
| Architecture | Widget-based declarative UI |
| Performance | 60/120 FPS native performance |

### Creating a Flutter Project

```bash
flutter create my_app
cd my_app
flutter run
```

### Project Structure

```
my_app/
  lib/
    main.dart      # Entry point
  test/            # Tests
  android/         # Android platform
  ios/             # iOS platform
  web/             # Web platform
  pubspec.yaml     # Dependencies
```

### Minimal Flutter App

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(const MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyApp({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: 'Flutter Demo',
      theme: ThemeData(
        colorSchemeSeed: Colors.blue,
      ),
      home: const MyHomePage(),
    );
  }
}

class MyHomePage extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyHomePage({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(title: const Text('Welcome')),
      body: const Center(
        child: Text('Hello, Flutter!'),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

### Key Concepts

| Concept | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Widgets | Everything is a widget |
| Build method | Describes UI configuration |
| State | Data that can change over time |
| RenderObject | Low-level rendering |
| Element | Widget instance in tree |

> **Key Point:** Flutter's `runApp()` takes a Widget and makes it the root of the widget tree. MaterialApp provides Material Design conventions. Flutter 3.x+ supports all major platforms.

